ADDITIONAL_DESCRIPTION:
• Series : EBE
  • Product Lines : Industrial Tools
  • Your fast, safe and simple solution for cutting metal bar
  • The versatile EBE-Series Electric Bar Cutters quickly cut through heavy duty bar up to 1.02 inches in diameter without the need for an external hydraulic pump
  • Their compact size and low weight enable them to be easily transported and used wherever an external power source is available
  • The EBE-Series Cylinder is driven by a radial pump powered by an electric motor
  • Highly durable, long-lasting blades outlast angle grinder or saw blades
  • Controlled cutting process enhances user safety compared with use of cut-off blades
  • Minimal spark risk compared to torching, grinding and sawing methods
  • Cutters produce minimal vibration, helping prevent HAVS (Hand Arm Vibration Syndrome)
  • Safety guard helps protect hands from injury.
  • Piston-release mechanism allows blade to be reset, reducing jamming and providing a controlled cutting process
  • ETL certification applies to 120 Volt tools only

• Series : EBH
  • Product Lines : Industrial Tools
  • Your fast, safe and simple solution for cutting metal bar
  • The EBH-Series Hydraulic Bar Cutters are driven by a specialized external hydraulic pump for optimal power and a higher duty cycle compared with other cutter types. These cutters are ideal for use in production or manufacturing facilities with demanding, high-volume cutting applications.
  • The EBH-Series Hydraulic Cutters are designed to work with ZE6410X-Series electric pumps. Pump models vary by voltage type.
  • Highly durable, long-lasting blades outlast angle grinder or saw blades
  • Controlled cutting process enhances user safety compared with use of cut-off blades
  • Minimal spark risk compared to torching, grinding and sawing methods
  • Cutters produce minimal vibration, helping prevent HAVS (Hand Arm Vibration Syndrome)
  • Safety guard helps protect hands from injury.
  • Double-acting cylinder with advance and retract buttons improves control and reduces jamming
  • External hydraulic pump helps keep the tool cool, improving operational time (pump and hose sold separately).

• Series : ECCE
  • Product Lines : Industrial Tools
  • Your simple solution for cutting high-strength industrial chain
  • ECCE-Series Electric Chain Cutters are ideal for applications where safety is paramount. Unlike other cutting methods, Enerpac’s chain cutters cut chain links behind an enclosed, transparent safety guard, protecting the operator’s hands from potential injury while allowing the operator to monitor the cutting process.
  • Their compact size and low weight enable them to be easily transported and used wherever an external power source is available
  • The ECCE-Series Cylinder is driven by a radial pump powered by an electric motor
  • Quickly cut through heavy-duty chain links with minimal effort
  • Highly durable blades outlast angle grinder or saw blades
  • Controlled cutting process behind a protective shield enhances safety
  • Minimal spark risk compared to torching, grinding and sawing methods
  • Cutters produce minimal vibration, helping prevent HAVS (Hand Arm Vibration Syndrome)
  • Transparent safety guard protects hands and allows continuous monitoring for better management of cutting process.
  • Double-acting cylinder improves control and reduces jamming (ECCE32 models only)
  • ETL certification applies to 120 Volt tools only

• Series : EDCH
  • Product Lines : Industrial Tools
  • Powerful jaws and an exceptionally large blade aperture enable use on a large variety of applications including metal tubes, cables, profiles and similar materials
  • Shear-style blades make quick cuts
  • Minimal spark risk compared with torching, grinding and sawing methods
  • Cutters produce minimal vibration, helping prevent HAVS (Hand Arm Vibration Syndrome)
  • The EDCH-Series Hydraulic Cutters are designed to work with ZE6410M-Series electric pumps. Pump models vary by voltage type. Pump, hose and pump coupler set are all sold separately, and all are required for the system to function.
  • Durable blades maintain efficiency throughout rigorous use
  • Double-acting cylinder improves control and reduces jamming
  • Control knob immediately stops the tool when released, improving operator safety.
  • External hydraulic pump helps keep tool cooler and working longer (pump and hose sold separately).

• Series : EFBE
  • Product Lines : Industrial Tools
  • Cut high-tensile flat bar with ease
  • Highly durable, long-lasting blades offer increased longevity and less down time
  • Heavy-duty cutting head provides a longer operational life
  • Controlled cutting process enhances operator safety
  • Minimal spark risk compared with torching, grinding and sawing methods
  • Cutters produce minimal vibration, helping prevent HAVS (Hand Arm Vibration Syndrome)
  • EFBE-Series Electric Flat Bar Cutters enhance workplace safety by replacing unsafe cutting methods with a precise, controlled cutting solution
  • Unlike standard bar cutters, the deep cutting head design accommodates metal bar up to 2¾ inch (70 mm) high and over 0.59 inch (15 mm) thick
  • A piston release mechanism allows the blade to be stopped and reset at any time, providing the operator with a high degree of cutting precision and control
  • EFBE-Series Cutters are perfect for use in industrial manufacturing facilities as well as steel and metal fabrication shops
  • EFBE-Series Cylinder is driven by a radial hydraulic pump powered by an electric motor
  • ETL certification applies to 120 Volt tools only.

• Series : EWCH
  • Product Lines : Industrial Tools
  • Your quick and clean way to cut cable and wire rope
  • The EWCH-Series Hydraulic Wire and Cable Cutters are ideal for use in production facilities where demanding, high volume cutting applications are often encountered.
  • Each tool is driven by a specialized external hydraulic pump, which provides greater cutting force and allows for higher duty cycles compared with other cutter types.
  • The EWCH-Series Hydraulic Cutters are designed to work with ZE6410X-Series electric pumps. Pump models vary by voltage type.
  • Controlled cutting process enhances operator safety
  • Minimal spark risk compared with torching, grinding and sawing methods
  • Cutters produce minimal vibration, helping prevent HAVS (Hand Arm Vibration Syndrome)
  • Guillotine-style blades maintain effectiveness throughout rigorous use.
  • Cutting head can be opened and closed to help position material to be cut
  • Double-acting cylinder with advance and retract buttons improves control and reduces jamming
  • External hydraulic pump helps keep tool cooler and working longer (pump and hose sold separately)

• Series : ZE
  • Product Lines : Industrial Tools
  • A specialty Enerpac ZE6-Series electric pump model provides the precise flow required by Enerpac's hydraulic cutters.
  • A specially adapted twin hose connects the pumps directly with the cutters, allowing for complete control from the cutters themselves
  • Controlled directly from cutter with no pendant required
  • Powered by an induction motor for industrial applications that require extended duty cycles
  • IP54 Rating for superior dust and water protection
  • Single-Stage Pump
  • Cutter tool, pump and hose are all sold separately, and all are required for the system to function.
